title: Natural Dye Kit Cochineal & Ground Madder Root (pink and orange) + Good Tee Unisex
description: Looking for something fun, guilt-free and creative to do? We’ve got a really GOOD project for you. Introducing our natural dye kit, complete with a Good Tee, gives the beginner dyer a perfect introduction into the beauty and wonder of creating colour from nature and customizing your own unique t-shirt.  The best part about this, is it’s sustainable, a guilt-free project, with minimal environmental impact.==============================Kit Contains:A t-shirt in any size you need with rubber bands. Comprehensive instructions in the kit will take you through the step by step process of preparing your fibres and dyeing with these dried dyestuffs.Included are the ingredients to dye around 2-3 medium adult t-shirts. To purchase additional tees, will be 50% discount automatic at checkout.Alum (a food safe ingredient made of potassium aluminum sulfate) as the mordant(for colourfast), and Gallnut, tannin powder made from the galls formed on oak trees, for pre-mordanting.Ground madder root (rubia tinctoria) for lovely peachy orange shades, and Cochineal (dactylopius coccus) for pink.Please note that the dyed fibres in the photos are not included. They are there to show you what colours you can expect to achieve with the dye.==============================Dye Contents:35 g alum, 25g gallnut, 15g madder, 7g cochineal

title: Natural Dye Kit Logwood & Osage Sawdust (purple & yellow) + Good Tee Unisex
description: Looking for something fun, guilt-free, and creative to do? We’ve got a really GOOD project for you. Introducing our natural dye kit, complete with a Good Tee, gives the beginner dyer a perfect introduction to the beauty and wonder of creating colour from nature and customizing your own unique t-shirt.  The best part about this is it’s sustainable, a guilt-free project, with minimal environmental impact.==============================Kit Contains:A t-shirt in any size you need and rubber bands. Comprehensive instructions in the kit will take you through the step-by-step process of preparing your fibres and dyeing with these dried dyestuffs.Included are the ingredients to dye around 2-3 medium adult t-shirts. To purchase additional tees, will be 50% discount automatic at checkout.Alum (a food-safe ingredient made of potassium aluminum sulfate) as the mordant(for colorfast), and Gallnut, tannin powder made from the galls formed on oak trees, for pre-mordanting.Logwood chips (haematoxylon campechianum), which yield gorgeous soft purples, osage sawdust (maclura pomifera) for yellow, Please note that the dyed fibres in the photos are not included. They are there to show you what colours you can expect to achieve with the dye.==============================Dye Contents:35 g alum, 25g gallnut,15g logwood, 15g osage sawdust

title: Indigo (blue)  Dye Kit + Good Tee Unisex
description: Looking for something fun, guilt-free and creative to do? We’ve got a really GOOD project for you. Introducing our Indigo dye kit, complete with a Good Tee, gives the beginner dyer a perfect introduction into the beauty and wonder of creating colour from nature and customizing your own unique t-shirt.  The best part about this is it’s sustainable, a guilt-free project, with minimal environmental impact. Indigo (indigofera tinctoria) species are the world's only source of natural, true, colourfast blue. A magical dyestuff that has been used around the world as a dye since pre-historic times, the culture and wonder that surrounds this plant is immense.Indigo cannot be dyed in the same way as other dyes, but must be used to create a "living" vat, which is achieved through a sort of fermentation process.==============================Kit Contains:A t-shirt in any size you need. Included are the ingredients to dye around 2-3 medium adult t-shirts and rubber bands. The kit also includes comprehensive instructions on how to create and use the vat. To purchase additional tees, will be 50% discount automatic at checkout.This kit contains the pre-measured ingredients to create one organic fructose vat, with which you can dye quite a bit of fibre - how much a kit will dye depends on a few things, including how dark you want the blue to be, and what fibres you use. But it will dye a lot! As a general ballpark, you could expect to dye at least 2-3 t-shirts to a medium blue, and probably more, and darker if you wish.indigofera tinctoria powder, extracted from the plant, pickling lime (calx), and fructose sugar.Please note that the dyed fibres in the photos are not included. They are there to show you what colours you can expect to achieve with the dye. ==============================Dye Contents:20g indigofera tinctoria powder, extracted from the plant, 40g pickling lime (calx), 60g fructose sugar.

title: Boyfriend Origins - Charcoal
description:
An effortlessly cool, oversized fit. We added length for a relaxed, vintage feel. Made with premium organic cotton, the Boyfriend Origins tee has an ultra-comfy worn-in feel, like an old band tee you've loved for years.

Original artwork, hand-drawn by hinterland artist Nelson Kokela, references the beautiful mountain ranges of our hinterland home. We pay tribute to the roots of Outland Denim, and the connection our community has with the seamstresses who make their clothes.

description:

title: High Hopes Tee
description:
We have high hopes. Hope for the future, for humanity, for our planet. We celebrate what is good in the world - the beauty of humanity. We’re not deterred by pessimism, neither are our heads in the clouds. We stay grounded but move forward with passion, vision, and purpose. We believe the clothes we wear can be a force for good. No one is perfect, but we commit to always fight for a better way. 

An effortlessly cool, oversized fit. We added some length for a relaxed, vintage feel. Made with premium organic cotton, the High Hopes tee has an ultra-comfy, worn-in feel, like an old band tee that you've loved for years.

Finished with original Outland Denim x Montana Lower ‘High Hopes’ artwork. The High Hopes tee design was produced in collaboration with Montana Lower. Designed for positive impact, made for a better tomorrow.

title: Humanity Tee - Black
description:
We made this tee for all the suckers for humanity, just like you. You're a sucker for extending a helping hand. A sucker for giving back. A sucker for lending your neighbor the mower (even though you'll never get it back). A sucker for seeing the good in people. A sucker for hope. A sucker for this beautiful planet we call home.

An effortlessly cool, oversized fit. We added some length for a relaxed, vintage feel. Made with premium organic cotton, the Humanity tee has a classic t-shirt structure. It has a crisper feeling in comparison to the Boyfriend tee, while still feeling incredibly soft to touch and features original artwork, hand-drawn by hinterland artist Nelson Nokela.

Released especially to raise awareness of social injustice this July 30, World Day Against Trafficking in Persons, this isn't just any tee. Wear with pride knowing that your Humanity tee provided life-transforming opportunity, education, and support to people who have experienced trafficking and exploitation.

title: Humanity Tee - White
description:
We made this tee for all the suckers for humanity, just like you. You're a sucker for extending a helping hand. A sucker for giving back. A sucker for lending your neighbor the mower (even though you'll never get it back). A sucker for seeing the good in people. A sucker for hope. A sucker for this beautiful planet we call home.

An effortlessly cool, oversized fit. We added some length for a relaxed, vintage feel. Made with premium organic cotton, the Humanity tee has a classic t-shirt structure. It has a crisper feeling in comparison to the Boyfriend tee, while still feeling incredibly soft to touch and features original artwork, hand-drawn by hinterland artist Nelson Nokela.

Released especially to raise awareness of social injustice this July 30, World Day Against Trafficking in Persons, this isn't just any tee. Wear with pride knowing that your Humanity tee provided life-transforming opportunity, education, and support to people who have experienced trafficking and exploitation.

title: Jane 1996 - Charcoal
description: Simple and chic, the Jane tee is a go-to relaxed and classic cut. Jane drapes beautifully and pairs perfectly with your favourite jeans or shorts. Made with soft-to-touch, premium organic cotton for maximum comfort and durability. Finished with a touch of ’90s, Jane features a small, centred Outland Denim logo.

title: Margot - White
description:
A quintessential crisp, white button-down with a modern twist. We’ve elevated an understated essential with a contemporary unstructured shape, high-low back, and drop-sleeve for a relaxed, effortlessly chic look that will carry from day to night. 

Pair with your denim for instant ‘off-duty model’ vibes, or tuck into our sophisticated Penny skirt for the 9-5.

title: Sam Raglan - Navy
description: An ode to old-school, the 100% organic cotton Sam raglan tee is an iconic core essential in your wardrobe. Made for clean and easy styling, with a boyfriend-style relaxed fit through the neck and body. Finished with heritage-inspired Outland Denim logo. Sam is great for layering under a jacket or simply wearing as-is. We recommend pairing with the Annie short in White or your Athina jeans for a 90’s inspired ensemble.

title: Sam Raglan - White
description: An ode to old-school, the 100% organic cotton Sam raglan tee is an iconic core essential in your wardrobe. title: Bernie - Ink
description:
Not too heavy, not too light, the Bernie jersey walks a perfect line down the middle. This makes it perfect for all-year-round wear. Throw on over a tee, layer under a jacket, or keep things simple and wear as is - either way, Bernie will serve you well.

Bernie’s 100% organic cotton waffle knit fabric offers a more elevated alternative to your traditional crew, along with a super soft, breathable feel. We’ve finished Bernie with a Good For Humanity brand patch at the hip, because you deserve it.

title: Placement Origins - Charcoal
description:
The Placement Origins tee has a classic shape through the body with extra length for a relaxed, vintage feel. Made from premium organic cotton for perfect weight and softness.

This original artwork, hand-drawn by hinterland artist Nelson Kokela, references the beautiful mountain ranges of our hinterland home. Here we pay tribute to the roots of Outland Denim, and the connection our community has with the seamstresses who make their clothes.

title: The Boxy Crew

title: Women's Organic Long Sleeve Crew Neck T-shirt
description: A quintessential staple in any organic wardrobe - the classic Long Sleeve Crew Neck Tee. In addition to its fair trade credentials, what sets this one apart is the fabric. A substantial blend of organic Peruvian Pima cotton (among the finest in the world) with a hint of spandex yields a beautiful drape and enduring resilience. With long lasting Pima cotton, you can rest assured your tee will look and feel great for years to come.

The T-shirt is so soft on the skin that the wearer can feel summer and awaken a desire for warm days.

title: HARRY Short-sleeved shirt
description: Soft and kind to the skin: short-sleeved vest made of 70% living wool (from controlled biological livestock) and 30% silk. Temperature equalizing, seamless and very comfortable. GOTS certified.
